-- Deutsche Bank Says Crude Prices May Reach $100, Gas May Touch $6 by 2015
-- B y   E d w a r d   K l u m p
-- 2010-11-18T15:44:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-18/deutsche-bank-says-crude-prices-may-reach-100-gas-may-touch-6-by-2015.html
Oil prices may reach $100 a barrel
by 2015, Adam Sieminski, chief energy economist at Deutsche
Bank, said today at a conference in Houston. Natural-gas prices
might reach $6 per million British thermal units in that
timeframe, he said.  Sieminski, speaking at the 2010 Deloitte Oil & Gas
Conference, said he foresees oil at $80 a barrel in 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edward Klump in Houston at 
 eklump@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
